  "decision_conditions": [
    "<p>The development hereby permitted must be begun not later than the expiration of three years beginning with the date of this permission.</p><p><br></p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\nREASON: In order to comply with the provisions of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended).</p><p>\r\n</p>",
    "&lt;p&gt;The following elements of the scheme shall not be installed, implemented or carried out unless in accordance with details which shall have been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.&amp;nbsp; The works shall not be carried out otherwise than in accordance with the approved details.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;a) Details of all new and replacement sash windows, including a 1:20 scale elevation drawing of each window type showing the glazing pattern and lintels, and 1:5 scale vertical and horizontal cross section drawings showing the upper and lower stiles, the meeting rails, the dimensions of the glazing, the profile and dimensions of the glazing bars and spacers (if any).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;b) Details of new rooflights to the mansard including 1:20 elevation drawing, and 1:5 cross sections showing the location of the rooflight in relation to the roof structure and covering&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;c) Details of materials for the proposed mansard&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;REASON: To preserve the character and appearance of the Conservation Area under Section 72 of the Planning (Listed Buildings and Conservation Areas) Act 1990 and National Planning Policy Framework, December 2024, Paragraphs 207 to 221; The London Plan 2021 Policy HC1 Heritage conservation and growth; and Hackney Local Plan 2033, Policies LP1 Design Quality and Local Character, LP3 Designated Heritage Assets and LP4 Non Designated Heritage Assets.&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;All new and replacement sash windows shall accurately replicate, in terms of material, profile and detailing, the historic window design of the terrace. They shall be painted timber, double-hung sash windows with a slim profile and narrow integral (not applied) glazing bars with a putty finish (not timber bead). The glazing shall be no greater than 12mm (4mm glass : 4mm gas : 4mm glass) in total thickness. No trickle vents or metallic/perforated spacer bars are permitted.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;REASON: To preserve the character and appearance of the Conservation Area under Section 72 of the Planning (Listed Buildings and Conservation Areas) Act 1990 and National Planning Policy Framework, December 2024, Paragraphs 207 to 221; The London Plan 2021 Policy HC1 Heritage conservation and growth; and Hackney Local Plan 2033, Policies LP1 Design Quality and Local Character, LP3 Designated Heritage Assets and LP4 Non Designated Heritage Assets.&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;Prior to the first occupation of the development hereby approved a minimum of one Swift nesting bricks and/or boxes shall be provided at or close to eaves level of the development hereby approved. The bricks/boxes shall be retained thereafter in perpetuity.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;REASON: In the interests of biodiversity&lt;/p&gt;",
    "<p>The Development hereby permitted shall only be carried out and completed strictly in accordance with the submitted plans hereby approved and any subsequent approval of details.\r\n</p><p><br></p><p>\r\nREASON: To ensure that the development hereby permitted is carried out in full accordance with the plans hereby approved.\r\n</p>"
  ],
